Create A Skeleton Survey

Source: R/panel_create.R
panel_create.Rd

Create A Skeleton Survey

panel_create(survey_list, id_vars = c("uniqid", "doi"))

Arguments

survey_list

A list of data frames containing surveys.
id_vars

A vector of ID variables to form a panel ID var, defaults to c("uniqid", "doi").

Value

A tibble with the number of original ID vars and their panel_id as their concatenation for several surveys.

See also

Other harmonization functions: convert_class(), eurobarometer_special_values(), harmonize_qb_vars(), harmonize_value_labels(), id_create()

Examples

data (ZA7576_sample)
data (ZA6863_sample)
data (ZA5913_sample)

survey_list <- list ( 'ZA7576_sample' = ZA7576_sample,
                      'ZA6863_sample' = ZA6863_sample,
                      'ZA5913_sample' = ZA5913_sample)

panel_create (survey_list, id_vars =c("uniqid", "doi") )
